ata-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528051\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gvn1665702978897.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gvn1665702978897.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gvn1665702978897.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gvn1665702978897\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Link Information\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">On some operating systems, the installation program asks for a link information line. The installation program incorporates this line in the link command files that link Uniface applications or the Uniface Server.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62846e1_d62847e1_d62848e1\">The link information line is specific to your operating system. Refer to the documentation for your operating system and linker for more information about conventions, syntax, and so on.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62849e1_d62850e1_d62851e1\">With most operating systems, the link command file consists of a link command followed by a list of object files and object libraries. The text that you specify as the link information line is inserted in the list at the appropriate place.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62852e1_d62853e1_d62854e1\">On the link information line you must specify the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__li_d27437e1_d27438e1_d27439e1\">The object file or files, or library containing the DBMS connector\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__li_d27440e1_d27441e1_d27442e1\">The object libraries that are required to link with the API of the DBMS\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62855e1_d62856e1_d62857e1\">You do not need to specify the standard operating system object libraries, because either the Uniface installation program inserts these in the link command file, or the linker uses them automatically.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62858e1_d62859e1_d62860e1\">You can use the link command file generated by the installation program to construct link command files or ‘make files’ in your development environment.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__section_klr_rkj_kcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1079578e76\">Full Path Specification</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvn1665702978897__p_d62864e1_d62865e1_d62866e1\">The object files and libraries on the link information\n        line must be preceded by a full directory path, or by an environment variable or logical\n        specifying the path. You must define the environment variables or logicals whenever you link\n        a Uniface application or Uniface Server that uses the user-defined connector. It is a good\n        idea to define these environment variables or logicals in a systemwide logon command file.\n        For more information, consult your operating system documentation.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528051\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528051\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Link Information Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Link Information On some operating systems, the installation program asks for a link information line. The installation program incorporates this line in the link command files that link Uniface applications or the Uniface Server. The link information line is specific to your operating system. Refer to the documentation for your operating system and linker for more information about conventions, syntax, and so on. With most operating systems, the link command file consists of a link command followed by a list of object files and object libraries. The text that you specify as the link information line is inserted in the list at the appropriate place. On the link information line you must specify the following: The object file or files, or library containing the DBMS connector The object libraries that are required to link with the API of the DBMS You do not need to specify the standard operating system object libraries, because either the Uniface installation program inserts these in the link command file, or the linker uses them automatically. You can use the link command file generated by the installation program to construct link command files or ‘make files’ in your development environment. Full Path Specification The object files and libraries on the link information line must be preceded by a full directory path, or by an environment variable or logical specifying the path. You must define the environment variables or logicals whenever you link a Uniface application or Uniface Server that uses the user-defined connector. It is a good idea to define these environment variables or logicals in a systemwide logon command file. For more information, consult your operating system documentation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}